Speaking of scope: the scope is a Vortex Crossfire II 6-18x44 with the Dead Hold BDC reticle. Scope was just purchased in May. 

You'll notice that this action doesn't look like other Axis. The action came from a gunsmith who, as he said, "got bored at work one day so I worked on the trigger a bit". And yes, this was a real gunsmith, not Uncle Ted in his garage. I don't know what he did but it breaks clean and crisp! He put a spare 22-250 barrel (hence the stainless) on it and bedded the action into this stock (very comfortable stock!). I bought the rifle from him as a backup for my recent prairie dog trip to North Dakota, but I liked my .204 so much I put 100 rounds through this and left it in the truck. There is no detachable magazine with this. I won't lie, I lost it. You can purchase one and it will fit as the stock has the latch present. I've been using a piece of cardboard to make a shelf and loading it like a single shot. 

Comes with the bipod and sling, and the box the scope came in. Any questions, feel free to ask. I'm not here to screw anyone over. 

No, I WILL NOT SEPARATE THEM. Package deal only. Also, NO TRADES please. I don't mean to yell, just have to put it in big letters so people see it. Please don't read that and think, "well, maybe he'll want my trade". No. I won't. Don't ask. 

Paperwork will be done at the FFL of your choice, and paid for by you.
